{{Infobox NRHP | name = Clem's Opera House | nrhp_type = | image = Clems Opera House.JPG | caption = | location= Main and Post Sts., [[Gresham, Nebraska]] | coordinates = {{coord|41|1|41|N|97|24|7|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Nebraska#USA | built = c.1891 | architecture = Two-part [[commercial block]] | added = September 28, 1988 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | mpsub = {{NRHP url|id=64500391|title=Opera House Buildings in Nebraska 1867-1917 MPS}} | refnum = 88000949<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} '''Clem's Opera House''', at Main and Post Sts. in [[Gresham, Nebraska]], is a building constructed in about 1891. It has also been denoted '''NeHBS #YK04-1''' and '''OHBIN #03-01-02'''.
The opera house served as a venue for both touring and home-grown theatrical and musical performances, for lectures, and for movies. It also provided a location for community gatherings, including box socials, high-school commencements, farmer's institutes, and political-party meetings.<ref name=nomform>Ehlers, D. Layne. [http://www.nebraskahistory.org/histpres/nebraska/york/YK04-001_Clems_Opera_Hse.pdf "National Register of Historic Places Registration Form: Clem's Opera House".] [http://www.nebraskahistory.org/index.shtml Nebraska State Historical Society.] Retrieved 2013-10-18.</ref>
The building was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1988.<ref>[http://www.nebraskahistory.org/histpres/nebraska/york.htm "Nebraska National Register Sites in York County".] [http://www.nebraskahistory.org/index.shtml Nebraska State Historical Society.] Retrieved 2013-10-18.</ref>
